<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-402-124  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 402 124.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics Weekly  May 31 1989 n1463 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FOG lifts from aircraft navigation. (Fibre Optic Gyroscopes)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Payne, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Litton subsidiary Litef is flight testing aircraft navigationequipment that uses fiber optic gyroscopes (FOGs) rather thannormal mechanical gyros.andP;  FOGs could be cheaper to produce, buttheir most important advantages are likely to be theirinsensitivity to shock and their ability to work at very highrotation rates.andP;  Litef has built an attitude and heading referencesystem (AHRS) fitted with three FOGs, but applications depend onmilitary finding and future developments in munitions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Litton Industries Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     New ProductNavigationDesignFunctional CapabilitiesFiber OpticsProduct Development.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>